# CRUD Workflow Example

```sql
CREATE DATABASE company;

USE company;

CREATE TABLE employees (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    age INT
);

INSERT INTO employees VALUES (1, 'John', 25);

SELECT * FROM employees;

UPDATE employees
SET age = 26
WHERE id = 1;

DELETE FROM employees
WHERE id = 1;
```

---

# Best Practices

## 1. Always Use WHERE
Prevents accidental updates/deletes.

## 2. Validate Data Before Insert
Ensure proper data types.

## 3. Use Primary Keys
Prevents duplicates.

## 4. Backup Before Bulk Delete
Important for production systems.

